The paper deals with identification of dynamical systems, which is a topic in control theory and system identification. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization and statistical methods, which are relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The use of non-parametric models and weighted least squares also suggests relevance to neural networks and signal processing, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) possible sub-categories.
